text.tspan: Day of the year with peak cherry tree blossom in Kyoto, Japan
The vertical axis shows the date of peak blossom, expressed as the number of days since 1st January. The timing
of the peak cherry blossom is influenced by spring temperatures. Higher temperatures due to climate change
have caused the peak blossom to gradually move earlier in the year since the early 20th century.
